Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:12.04,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.48,0:00:21.68,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,So today, rather than us just talking,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.44,0:00:16.94,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.68,0:00:32.24,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,we really wanted you to see that scene. Thank you so much for sharing all your impressions in the comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.28,0:00:24.78,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.83,0:00:26.33,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:32.92,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,We really appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.92,0:00:42.30,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,With that story in mind, we'd like to talk a bit about how we approached our roles as actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.30,0:00:51.12,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,These are just some things we kept in mind while performing, so please keep that in mind as you listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.12,0:00:55.68,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,From Ena's perspective, regarding Episode 8...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.68,0:01:46.24,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Well, not just Episode 8, but looking back at the previous story too, I tried to put myself in Ena's shoes. I couldn't find a 'right' answer at all. I kept thinking about how she'd feel and act, staring at the script until we got to Episode 8. I found myself getting swept up in the emotional atmosphere of the event story and the direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.24,0:01:49.52,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,I just couldn't help but feel tearful,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.52,0:01:53.88,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,and the tears just kept welling up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.88,0:02:01.78,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,The script for Episode 8 always has notes on the nuances of how they want us to perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.78,0:02:06.74,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,There were detailed instructions like 'cry here' or 'sniffle here.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:17.88,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Based on that, I initially planned to play Ena as someone crying because she desperately wanted to tell Mizuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.88,0:02:25.16,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,'You're fine just as you are' and 'You're important to me.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.16,0:02:39.28,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,I wanted to perform with that honest feeling. But when I got to the recording, the direction I received was that they wanted a 'catfight.'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:45.16,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,When they said they wanted to see a catfight between Mizuki and Ena, I asked,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.16,0:02:48.88,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,'So I don't have to cry? I can actually fight?'
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.88,0:02:59.80,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,When I thought about what kind of Ena that would be, it hit me. The script literally says Ena hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.80,0:03:05.62,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,My initial plan and the notes in the script were lovely,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.62,0:03:20.14,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,but being overly careful because she cares so much about Mizuki didn't feel quite like Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.14,0:03:45.36,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Caring is important, but because she cares, it was more important for her to clash and have their usual arguments, like 'Why don't you get it?' Since I'm not actually Ena, looking at it from the outside made it feel like this grand, epic thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.36,0:03:49.96,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,The problem itself is certainly something only Mizuki can truly understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.96,0:03:55.52,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,But for the two of them, and for Ena, it was probably just a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.52,0:04:17.54,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,We might have made it seem like a huge deal from the outside, but I interpreted it as the first time these two truly clashed with someone they hadn't been able to be honest with before. That's how I approached the performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.54,0:04:34.37,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,I was worried because the illustration of an angry Ena didn't match what I'd imagined, but it turned out so wonderful that I'm really relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.37,0:04:34.94,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.94,0:04:38.04,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,So, that was Episode 8. Since we're here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:49.24,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Mizuki had a lot going on in this Episode 8 and the previous one, and there was that back-and-forth with Ena. I'd love to hear about that if we have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.24,0:04:49.98,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Do we have time?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.98,0:04:50.81,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.81,0:04:53.32,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,From Mizuki's perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:04:57.72,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,you can't miss either of those Episode 8s.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.72,0:05:02.78,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,In the previous Episode 8, Ena was mostly at a loss for words,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.78,0:05:07.37,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,so for me, that was all there was to it. How about you, Mizuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.37,0:05:07.96,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Mizuki-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.96,0:05:08.72,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.80,0:05:30.48,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,I don't think it's my place to say exactly what the character was thinking, so I'll talk about the technical side. For the previous event and this one, I debated until the very last minute whether to record standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:44.20,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,When it comes to voice acting, I'm the type who feels I need to perform with my whole body, so I thought standing would be better, like on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.20,0:06:18.90,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,But when you're crying, you lose strength in your legs. I decided it might be better to sit so I could focus entirely on the voice. For the previous Episode 8, my initial plan was to speak clearly even while crying, but the direction was to cry more. We did about three or four takes. I recorded without hearing Minori-chan's lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.90,0:06:25.14,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,both last time and this time. So I heard our full interaction at the same time as everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.14,0:06:28.46,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Seeing how it all came together as a finished work,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.46,0:06:36.08,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,I feel like I gave it my absolute all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:41.14,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,We see each other quite often, even if we don't record together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.14,0:06:42.28,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,We're always talking about things like, 'How did you record that?'
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.28,0:06:42.98,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,or 'What kind of direction did you get?'
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.98,0:06:46.32,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,This is a small request for the staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:49.64,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,but we've said it would be wonderful if we could record together in the same studio someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.64,0:06:58.02,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,The ProSeka staff really respect the actors' performances.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:07:10.66,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Mizuki and Ena have grown, and they might hit another big wall in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.66,0:07:13.12,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,or they might move to help someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.12,0:07:18.44,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,I hope we can record those kinds of wonderful scenes together next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:23.68,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,It's amazing how well it fit together without us being in the same room. We're pretty good, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.68,0:07:28.32,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Yeah! Anyway, that's what we wanted to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.32,0:07:34.28,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,It's almost time, so let's all watch the AfterLive together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.56,0:07:30.06,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.48,0:07:34.98,Suzuki Minori,host,0,0,0,,Private...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.00,0:07:34.98,Sato Hinata,host,0,0,0,,Yes.
